  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key legal definitions include:\n\n1. Basic components typically include:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to disguise the origins of criminal money\n\n2. Most jurisdictions recognize three main stages:\n- Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial systems\n- Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure origins\n- Integration: Reintroducing laundered money into legitimate economy\n\n3. Legal variations exist across different countries, but most definitions involve:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowledge of funds' criminal origins\n- Attempts to disguise illegal proceeds\n\n4. Common predicate crimes often include:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Organized crime activities\n\n5. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, with different thresholds and specific statutory requirements.\n\nI aim to provide general legal information without advocating for or assisting with any illegal activities.",
